law for financial institutions defining

00:00:28.755 --> 00:00:33.225
their powers, their functions, and
all the regulations they must follow.

00:00:33.735 --> 00:00:38.325
These laws are not just for sure,
they are the guardians of stability,

00:00:38.475 --> 00:00:43.394
the protectors of your money, and the
big wall that stops financial crimes.

00:00:43.905 --> 00:00:49.215
Let's start with the big boss, the
Reserve Bank of India Act 1934.

00:00:49.445 --> 00:00:51.125
Or the RBI Act.

00:00:51.575 --> 00:00:56.435
This is the act that gave birth to our
central bank, the Reserve Bank of India.

00:00:56.855 --> 00:01:02.135
It's the RBI's horoscope, you could say,
outlining all its powers, functions,

00:01:02.135 --> 00:01:07.355
and responsibilities from managing
monetary policy to keep inflation in

00:01:07.355 --> 00:01:12.065
check, to printing our beautiful currency
notes and bossing around other banks.

00:01:12.095 --> 00:01:13.595
It's all in this act.

00:01:14.255 --> 00:01:17.855
Next up is the Banking
Regulation Act of 1949.

00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:24.360
Or the BR Act if the RBI Act is the
king, this act is the Prime Minister

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:26.580
managing the daily administration.

00:01:27.030 --> 00:01:31.350
It provides the entire framework
for regulating and supervising

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:33.060
all banking companies in India.

00:01:33.660 --> 00:01:38.400
It covers everything from giving a
bank a license to open shop, to its

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:42.780
management, its daily operations,
and even what happens when banks

00:01:42.780 --> 00:01:45.509
merge or sadly have to be liquidated.

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:49.920
It's all about ensuring sound
and safe banking practices.

00:01:50.490 --> 00:01:55.800
Then we have a real old timer, the
Negotiable Instruments Act of 1881.

00:01:56.235 --> 00:02:01.125
This one deals with the tools of the
trade, things like promissory notes, bills

00:02:01.125 --> 00:02:03.705
of exchange, and the ever famous check.

00:02:04.185 --> 00:02:08.595
This act is the rule book for these
instruments specifying what makes them

00:02:08.595 --> 00:02:14.145
valid, who is liable if a check bounces
a very common headache, and the proper

00:02:14.235 --> 00:02:16.245
rules for transferring and paying them.

00:02:16.929 --> 00:02:18.730
Moving to more modern times.

00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:23.799
We have the mouthful that is the
Securitization and Reconstruction of

00:02:23.799 --> 00:02:29.709
Financial Assets and Enforcement of
Security Interest Act 2002, but we

00:02:29.709 --> 00:02:31.989
call it the Surfacey Act for short.

00:02:32.079 --> 00:02:36.730
Thank goodness this act is the
bank's superhero when it comes to

00:02:36.730 --> 00:02:39.489
bad loans or non-performing assets.

00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:44.220
It gives banks and financial
institutions the power to recover

00:02:44.220 --> 00:02:48.660
their money from Defaulters without
getting stuck in long court battles.

00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:53.970
It allows them to directly take control of
the assets that were put up as security.

00:02:54.570 --> 00:02:59.340
Then there's the prevention of
money Laundering Act 2002 or PML.

00:02:59.960 --> 00:03:03.530
This law is the financial
world's detergent designed

00:03:03.530 --> 00:03:05.090
to wash away dirty money.

00:03:05.510 --> 00:03:09.799
It was created to prevent the crime
of money laundering and allows for the

00:03:09.799 --> 00:03:15.140
confiscation of any property that came
from or was used in such activities.

00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:20.329
Crucially, it makes it mandatory for
banks to be detectives and report

00:03:20.390 --> 00:03:22.730
any suspicious transactions they see.

00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:26.650
Finally, we have the Foreign
Exchange Management Act of

00:03:26.650 --> 00:03:29.350
1999, also known as fema.

00:03:29.770 --> 00:03:33.730
This act replaced an older,
stricter law and is all about

00:03:33.730 --> 00:03:35.230
managing foreign currency.

00:03:35.590 --> 00:03:40.720
Its main goal is to make life easier
for external trade and payments, and

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:44.890
to promote a healthy, well-maintained
foreign exchange market in India.

00:03:45.610 --> 00:03:46.840
Real world relevance.

00:03:47.295 --> 00:03:50.925
So why should you a future
banking professional care

00:03:50.925 --> 00:03:52.665
about these dusty old laws?

00:03:52.935 --> 00:03:59.055
Well, understanding the RBI Act 1934
helps you grasp why the Central Bank

00:03:59.055 --> 00:04:03.585
issue certain directives, and how
its monetary policy decisions will

00:04:03.645 --> 00:04:05.715
affect your bank's day-to-day work.

00:04:06.225 --> 00:04:10.755
The Banking Regulation Act 1949
is literally the foundation

00:04:10.755 --> 00:04:12.345
of all banking operations.

00:04:12.645 --> 00:04:16.935
It dictates how banks get licensed,
how they are managed, and how they

00:04:16.935 --> 00:04:21.055
conduct business making compliance
a huge part of any banking role.

00:04:21.905 --> 00:04:27.215
